name: molly conger
tweet: it's time for the first meeting of charlottesville's parking advisory panel since before the pandemic began! what an exciting afternoon!  https://t.co/MS24xVE0YS

name: molly conger
tweet: brand new member of the parking advisory panel @jakefmooney is on the call! i don't see @jbouie yet.

name: molly conger
tweet: at their work session earlier this month, council agreed to transition the parking advisory panel from a council advisory board to a staff advisory board. i'm not sure an official vote on this has actually taken place yet?  https://t.co/Fnw91xMv92

name: molly conger
tweet: there has been a little turnover on the board, so there is currently no chair. joan fenton suggests choosing a temporary chair from the returning members then holding an election in a meeting or two for a longterm chair. kirby hutto will be temporary chair.

name: molly conger
tweet: rick siebert, the city's parking director, asked brian wheeler at the top of the meeting if recording the meetings was an acceptable substitute for taking minutes. it isn't. minutes are legally required for public bodies, but as a staff advisory body they wouldn't have to, right?

name: molly conger
tweet: introduction time - new members jakes mooney, jamelle bouie, and danny yoder introduce themselves to the other members of the panel. joan fenton introduces herself - "i own my own parking lot, so i have no problem parking, but i sympathize with all the other parking issues."

name: molly conger
tweet: hutto says tourists, students, and others coming downtown "for dinner and a show" are not likely to choose public transportation, so parking is necessary for the economic health of downtown.

name: molly conger
tweet: kirby hutto says he is concerned about the "chipping away" of parking downtown, specifically citing the loss of 50 parking spaces to the belmont bridge project. he's very excited about the new garage.

name: molly conger
tweet: mike rodi says although he likes to bike and walk, "we are still a community that is heavily reliant on cars."  michael cusano is a relatively recent transplant, having lived here for just a year. he says he only goes downtown for "entertainment and food."

name: molly conger
tweet: why is everyone on the parking advisory panel originally from new york? what is going on here. does being from new york cause some genetic anxiety about parking?

name: molly conger
tweet: a member asks if they're going to have a public comment period, indicating that a few hands are raised... rick siebert says he doesn't think it's required (by which he means he would prefer not to hear from the public) other members of the panel seem willing to hear it

name: molly conger
tweet: rick says if they have to have public comment, it should be at the end so questions asked by the public don't cause redundant conversations to be had. a motion is made, seconded, and passed unanimously.

name: molly conger
tweet: oh, parking is free in the garages every weekend. from friday 10pm to early monday morning. this is apparently a COVID thing. i guess i haven't been downtown much in the last 7 months...

name: molly conger
tweet: people with monthly parking passes are being allowed to suspend their monthly garage pass during this time. (because of the wait list of over 100 people, simply terminating it would mean you can't get it back)

name: molly conger
tweet: willow tree moved out of downtown & worldstrides declared bankruptcy & fired a ton of people - both of these events freed up a lot of monthly parking passes. siebert hopes this will eliminate much of the waiting list.

name: molly conger
tweet: siebert is still pursuing the idea of an RFP to hire a company that would do parking enforcement on a contract basis. he says the chief of police is "not at all supportive" of the idea.

name: molly conger
tweet: we've been having this exact same conversation with no movement at all for a very long time   https://t.co/M1DYCh16Wt

name: molly conger
tweet: siebert says the police chief's problem with the idea is that the public may not respect a civilian parking enforcement officer "and there may be assaults" AND "the police will still be blamed for the tickets"

name: molly conger
tweet: "no person operating a bureaucracy ever wants part of the duties of that bureaucracy taken away," siebert says, explaining why he thinks the police chief doesn't want a private company writing parking tickets.

name: molly conger
tweet: joan fenton says parking enforcement has been a problem (in that it isn't done at all) and when it is done, there have been issues with officers being rude. "this is something the police do not need to be doing."

name: molly conger
tweet: hutto agrees & supports putting out an RFP for contract parking enforcement. mike rodi says the parking enforcement personnel would need official uniforms but uniforms that are clearly not law enforcement related, making them "less threatening."

name: molly conger
tweet: "i agree with rick - the police chief just didn't want to give up the responsibility," joan says. but the lack of enforcement is so consistent that people just assume they won't get tickets and violate parking rules.

name: molly conger
tweet: these private parking enforcement personnel would not be financially incentivized in any way for the number of tickets written. they would also not be armed.

name: molly conger
tweet: next is discussion of the 7th street garage, which i believe is an absolutely fucking insane expense under current conditions!!! we don't need more parking and we don't have $15mil!

name: molly conger
tweet: as part of an agreement between the city & the county, the county will keep their courthouses in their current historic location in court square. in return, the city has to provide 90 dedicated downtown parking spaces. so... we're gonna build a whole parking garage.

name: molly conger
tweet: the city has hired a parking consultant to ensure the garage gets constructed, siebert says. the city will put out an RFQ for firms who can do this as a design-build project. 3-5 companies will be chosen & they'll all submit proposals.

name: molly conger
tweet: (remember, lucky 7 and guadalajara will be demolished for this parking garage, which is to be built across the street from the market street parking garage)

name: molly conger
tweet: siebert says the final garage will have 10,000ft of street front retail and 250+ parking spots. the project has to be by-right - there is concern that any need for variances to be granted will slow it down & we won't meet our obligation to the county.

name: molly conger
tweet: siebert says they are "having a kickoff meeting tomorrow" with the consultant to "work on finalizing a timeline." the RFQ and RFP have not been written. the obligation to the county is due fall 2023.

name: molly conger
tweet: if the city fails to deliver, they have to give the county back the half of the surface lot they bought from the county & the county gets to use the entire ground floor of an existing garage (missed whether he said market or water, but water would be a lot more spots)

name: molly conger
tweet: "part of this MOA with the county was real poison pills for the city if they fail to live up to their end of the bargain, so failure is not an option," siebert says of the agreement with the county.

name: molly conger
tweet: ew rick siebert just asked joan fenton to smile

name: molly conger
tweet: ok so if we fail to spent $15mil to get them 90 parking spaces in a brand new garage, we have to give then 100 spaces in an existing garage? that seems... not that bad. rick made it sound like it was suicide.   https://t.co/j9EWk4hgAw

name: molly conger
tweet: i mean there were REPEATED discussions last year about whether it would be legal for them to prohibit disabled employees from using up all the disabled parking spots.   https://t.co/KAKG0QC8oQ

name: molly conger
tweet: this is a recurring theme - rick is always talking about parking being "eaten up" by people who work downtown. where are the people who make & serve the food at those restaurants supposed to park?

name: molly conger
tweet: the new garage will (perhaps) have solar arrays on the roof. apparently there is new technology available now so that when you hose down the concrete, the water that ends up down the sewer isn't full of gas & oil.

name: molly conger
tweet: time for public comment! first up is @RoryStolzenberg. he says he encourages staff to seek a rezoning to downtown extended NOW to get out ahead of this project - it would allow more by right use than the current zoning for that area.

name: molly conger
tweet: but his main comment is about PARKLETS! i think these are very cute! i bet the parking advisory panel would find them horrifying. imagine - LOSING A PARKING SPOT!    https://t.co/Nrj2E7DI8l

name: molly conger
tweet: it may shock you to hear that there are no further takers for public comment for the parking advisory panel.   joan fenton says she is in favor of parklets & other ways to create safe outdoor dining space. jason ness says the virginian on the corner has used them.

name: molly conger
tweet: one of the real barriers to creating parklets is... hills! not all of our streets are flat. you need a flat street for a dining area.

name: molly conger
tweet: oh it's like the wild west out here, rory is back on! he says there's no harm just giving restaurants the ability to have the parklets, rather than charging them by the day. it's not a lot of $ to the city, but restaurants may be unwilling to take any risk right now.

name: molly conger
tweet: kirby hutto says "whether they want it or not," council needs advice about parking (ok but council decided they won't take advice from the panel anymore - it's being transitioned to a staff advisory body)

name: molly conger
tweet: someone tried to move to adjourn, but jake would like additional clarification on the status of the parking advisory panel as a body - who are they giving advice to and is it wanted?

name: molly conger
tweet: joan fenton cites as one of the board's achievements forcing the city to change a planned bike lane on monticello that "saved" 14 parking spaces   https://t.co/wl1IQEepaM

name: molly conger
tweet: city communications director brian wheeler explains council's decision at the work session earlier this month to make this a staff advisory body - council would no longer make appointments or hear reports from the body. the city manager requested that its meetings remain open.

name: molly conger
tweet: council has not yet taken action on the decisions made during the october 6 work session - they'll vote on that next month.  again, john blair has said that the body will continue to publicly notice & hold public meetings, although they would not longer be required to by law.

name: molly conger
tweet: ok this time no one interrupted the motion to adjourn and this meeting of the parking advisory panel is over.

name: molly conger
tweet: (to be clear, i'm making a joke and it's good, actually, that jake asked what the point actually is of the body he was just appointed to! rick's explanation of council's decision at the top of the meeting was inaccurate & insufficient)
